post_text:
Hs volleyball at Emerson 6pm

Fan and team procedures:

Team and fans will be entering there own entrance located on the northwest gym doors. Each player has given a list of 4 people allowed at the game. These are the only fans allowed. 5$ for adults and 4$ for children. They ask to try and bring exact total so less handling of money is happening. Masks will be worn by all fans. Please bring masks.

Our team will travel dressed and go directly to the teams bench we will not use locker rooms. Masks will be worn at all times until playing. Bench players and coaches will wear masks. Players on the court will not wear masks. Our team and fans will leave the facility at the conclusion of the game. No hand shakes between teams will happen.

We are taking a lot of precautions. Please understand we have been in contact with local health department and E-H administration. Any cases of Covid were contained at the elementary level. The elementary and JH/HS are separated facilities across town.

Thank you all for following these guidelines! #bagopride

Alert:
Due to the majority of the teams in our All Nations High School Football league unable to participate in fall sports, the conference has voted to move the football season to the spring with an April start for games. We are in the process of petitioning the NSAA to allow our student-athletes this opportunity.

All other fall activities are still a go as planned:
HS cross country and volleyball practice start August 17th
JH cross country, football, and volleyball practice will start August 31st
You can pick up a code of conduct packet at the front desk.

post_text:
Winnebago Public School's High School Graduation will take place on Saturday, August 1, at 2:00. We are aware of the loss of a community member and express our condolences to the family. We have received permission from the family to continue with the graduation ceremony for the Class of 2020. The ceremony was originally scheduled to take place at the Pow-wow grounds; however, due to the funeral, it has been moved to the WPS school gym.

With the current Public Health and Safety Measures in place, Winnebago Public School's High School Graduation Ceremony has been limited to invited guests only. Students have submitted their guest lists and the individuals on that list are the only people who will be admitted. All guests will be required to wear masks and sit in an assigned area.

If you have any questions please contact Mr. Fehringer at the school.

post_text:
Yesterday the school board met to discuss the results of the parent/teacher surveys, the school calendar(s), the return to learn plan, and activities. As a result of the meeting, the school board reached a decision for the student start date to be September 8th, which will become official on Monday, August 3rd at a special board meeting. The school calendar, return to learn plan, and a decision regarding activities will be approved and released to the community and staff after it becomes official.

A virtual tour of the school, that will include health and safety measures will be released. Student homebound/in person orientation days will be set up before the start of the school year. The virtual tour video and orientation information will be shared with the community the week of August 10th.

A virtual tour of the school, that will include health and safety measures will be released. Student homebound/in person orientation days will be set up before the start of the school year. NOTICE OF MEETING OF THE BOARD OF EDUCATION
DISTRICT 17
WINNEBAGO, NEBRASKA

The regular meeting of the Board of Education (the ‚ÄúBoard‚Äù) of Thurston County School District 0017 (Winnebago Public Schools) in the State of Nebraska (the ‚ÄúDistrict‚Äù) will be held at 12:00 PM, Tuesday, June 23, 2020 in the regular meeting place of the Board, the School Conference Room on Highway 77 & 75 in the Village of Winnebago, Nebraska. The Board of Education will have the opportunity to meet via zoom, call in or in person in the board room. COVID-19 Health Mandate Requirements regarding Social Distancing will be followed. An agenda, kept continuously current, is available for public inspection in the offices of the District Superintendent, located at Highway 77 & 75, 878-2224. The meeting will be open to the attendance of the public. The meeting will be open to the attendance of the public via Face Book Live. See the WPS website or WPS Facebook Page for information regarding the live feed.

Due to a death in the community the June Board meeting was rescheduled.

post_text: WPS Class of 2020 Senior Spotlight - Marissa Marie Picotte is the daughter of Marcel Picotte and Clarissa Hoffman. While in high school, Marissa participated in volleyball, basketball, choir, and robotics. Her favorite school lunch is grilled cheese sandwich and tomato soup. Marissa‚Äôs favorite teacher is, ‚ÄúMr. Mette because he made art fun and something everyone enjoyed doing.‚Äù Her most memorable moments were winning the Outstanding Artist two years in a row at the Big Show in Wakefield, Nebraska. In the Fall, Marissa plans to attend Wayne State College where she will study Psychology. Her advice to underclassmen is, ‚ÄúPay attention in class and study. Don‚Äôt be afraid to try new things and make new friends. Make school fun!‚Äù

post_text: WPS Class of 2020 Senior Spotlight - Rosalio Rios, Jr. is the son of Trina Aldrich. While in high school, Lio participated in cross country and basketball. Lio‚Äôs most memorable moments were made during his freshman year when he was a member of the basketball team, something he regrets not sticking with. ‚ÄúIt was always laughs and goofy moments.‚Äù Lio‚Äôs favorite school lunch is lasagna and his favorite teacher is Mrs. Sanford. ‚ÄúShe was always quick to help - not just with me, but with the other students as well. And, she would always get my head right when she saw I was slacking.‚Äù In the Fall, Lio plans to study business at Western Iowa Tech. After receiving his Associate‚Äôs Degree, he plans to attend a University where he intends to eventually earn a Master‚Äôs Degree. Lio‚Äôs message to others is to ‚Äúnot take anything for granted,‚Äù and make your family proud. ‚ÄúThe only person that could get it done is you - no one else! Always remember, God isn‚Äôt about to put you through something you can‚Äôt handle. Tell yourself that when you feel like giving up.‚Äù

post_text: WPS Class of 2020 Senior Spotlight - Whisper WhiteTwin is the daughter of Danielle Greene. Her favorite school lunch is spaghetti, and her favorite staff member is Mrs. Tremayne because, ‚Äúbecause she was always nice to me & made me feel like I belonged..‚Äù The most memorable thing about high school for Whisper, was completing her graduation requirements and finishing a semester early. Whisper plans on going to college at some point and studying either Archaeology or Substance Abuse Counseling. Whisper would like to share this advice with underclassmen: ‚ÄúEveryone needs a friend in school, so don‚Äôt be shy to meet new people. Always make your peers feel welcomed & involved. Ask for help when you need it & turn in your assignments on time cuz it will give you more free time to do the things you want. You can accomplish anything you put your mind to. Never give up on your dreams & enjoy the rest of high school cuz that‚Äôs when reality hits. But the future is yours & I believe every single one of you will do great things. Stay positive.‚Äù

The only work that must be returned to the school is any work that was
received in an envelope labeled "Late Work." These assignments need to
be returned to the school; you can do so in one of the following ways:
1. Fax to the school: 402-878-2472 (then we will scan and email to teacher)

3. Take Pictures with a phone and email to the teacher.

All teachers email addresses can be found on the WPS website under the
"Staff" Tab: winnebagopublicschools.org

Work that is being sent home weekly is intended to be Reinforcement
and Enrichment work. If students would like this work to be used to
improve their current grade, it should be submitted in the same
manner.

We are asking that the actual papers not be returned to the school, as
we are trying to do our part to flatten the curve and slow the spread
of the Covid-19 Virus.

Thank you and stay healthy!

Parent(s)/Guardian(s)

WPS staff continues to work hard to ensure that the children receive breakfast and lunch along with educational packets. WPS is also trying to minimize the amount of traffic and staff hours to help control the spread of the COVID-19 Virus. If you are picking up lunches and/or educational packets, please pick up by 1:00 p.m.

A reminder: WPS will deliver breakfast and lunch on Mondays. WPS will deliver only once Tuesday through Thursday. This delivery will include lunch for that day and breakfast for the next morning. There is only a lunch delivery on Fridays. Delivery of lunches could take over 2 hours. Please have someone watching for the school vans. If you have dogs that are roaming outside your residence, our staff may not be able to deliver the lunches or packets.

Parents/Guardians- If you have a student at WPS in grades K-12, educational packets are being made for each and every student. If you are able to stop and pick your students packet up, please do on Monday of every week. These will be produced as long as we are out of school. If transportation is unavailable, please call the school and they will be delivered.

All students in grades 7-12 will be receiving invitations to zoom meetings from their teachers. These meetings are designed to be teachers' "Virtual Office Hours," so you will have some face-to-face time. Teachers will be available to meet with you to answer any questions you may have regarding late work and packet work.
Of course you can email your teachers anytime between the hours of 8-3 to receive assistance as well. Remember, all teachers' emails can be found on the Winnebago Public School website.

DISTRICT 17

WINNEBAGO, NEBRASKA

A special meeting of the Board of Education (the ‚ÄúBoard‚Äù) of Thurston County School District 0017 (Winnebago Public Schools) in the State of Nebraska (the ‚ÄúDistrict‚Äù) will be held at 12:00 PM, Tuesday, March 24, 2020 in the regular meeting place of the Board, the School Conference Room on Highway 77 & 75 in the Village of Winnebago, Nebraska. The Board of Education will have the opportunity to meet via zoom or in person in the board room. COVID-19 requirements of Social Distancing and the no more than 10 people in a setting will be followed. An agenda, kept continuously current, is available for public inspection in the offices of the District Superintendent, located at Highway 77 & 75, 878-2224. The meeting will be open to the attendance of the public via Face Book Live. See the WPS website or WPS Facebook Page for information regarding the live feed.

8:30am is the cut off for the daily count and calls received after 8:30am will be for the next serving day.

Breakfast is available curbside pick-up between 8-9am with delivery upon request. Lunch is pick-up or delivery from 11-1pm.
